# Installation Guide

## 1. Clone repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/financial-document-analyzer.git

cd financial-document-analyzer
```

---

## 2. Create virtual environment

```bash
python -m venv .venv

.venv\Scripts\activate
```

---

## 3. Install dependencies

```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## 4. Setup environment variables

Create `.env`

```text
GEMINI_API_KEY=your_api_key_here
```

Get key from:

https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey

---

# Install Redis (Windows)

Download:

https://github.com/tporadowski/redis/releases

Extract and run:

```bash
redis-server.exe
```

Verify:

```bash
redis-cli ping
```

Output:

```text
PONG
```

---

# Running the System

Open 3 terminals:

---

Terminal 1:

```bash
redis-server
```

---

Terminal 2:

```bash
celery -A worker worker --pool=solo --loglevel=info
```

---

Terminal 3:

```bash
uvicorn main:app --reload
```

---

# API Documentation

Open:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs
```

Swagger UI provides interactive API testing.

---

# API Endpoints

---

## 1. Upload and Analyze Document

POST

```text
/analyze
```

Request:

Form Data

file → PDF file

query → analysis question

Example:

```text
Analyze revenue and investment risks
```

Response:

```json
{
 "analysis_id": 1,
 "status": "processing"
}
```

---

## 2. Get Analysis Result

GET

```text
/result/{analysis_id}
```

Example:

```text
/result/1
```

Response:

```json
{
 "id": 1,
 "filename": "report.pdf",
 "query": "Analyze revenue",
 "result": "Revenue increased 12%",
 "status": "completed"
}
```

---

# Queue Worker Model (Bonus Requirement)

Implemented using:

Redis
Celery

Benefits:

Non-blocking API
Concurrent users supported
Scalable system
Background processing

---

# Database Integration (Bonus Requirement)

SQLite used to store:

Analysis ID
File name
Query
Result
Status

Provides persistent storage and retrieval.

---

# Example Workflow

Upload PDF → API creates task → Redis queue → Celery worker → Gemini analyzes → Result saved → User retrieves result

